Japan's biggest chemical maker Mitsubishi Kasei  Corp. announced Friday a pre-tax loss of 8.4 billion yen (82 million dollars)  for the year to March, reversing a profit of 8.3 billion yen a year earlier.
The company said sales declined 12 percent to 327 billion yen.
Mitsubishi expects to remain in the red this year, forecasting a further  loss of four billion yen despite increased sales of 330 billion yen.
